A &#39;void&#39; method should have some discernable effect on the system,
right?  Test the effect.

public class Counter {
    .
    .
    .
    public void incrementBy(int count) {
        this.counter += count;
    }
    .
    .
    .
}

public class CounterTest extends TestCase {
    .
    .
    .
    public void testIncrementBy() {
        Counter counter = new Counter();
        assertEquals(&quot;initial value&quot;, 0, counter.getCount());

        counter.incrementBy(5);
        assertEquals(&quot;incremented value&quot;, 5, counter.getCount());
    }
